The paper deals with lower bounds for the maximal size of permutation codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also connects permutation codes with linear block codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of techniques from linear algebra and optimization.
